# ====================================================================
# HOW TO GET YOUR CREDENTIALS:
# ====================================================================
#
# 1. API KEY:
#    - Go to https://developers.kite.trade/
#    - Sign in with Zerodha account
#    - Click "Create App" or view existing app
#    - Copy the API Key
#    - Paste it above as KITE_API_KEY value
#
# 2. ACCESS TOKEN:
#    - Run this Python code:
#
#      from kiteconnect import KiteConnect
#      kite = KiteConnect(api_key="YOUR_API_KEY")
#      print(kite.login_url())
#
#    - Open the URL in browser and login with Zerodha credentials
#    - You'll be redirected with code in URL like: code=XXXXX
#    - Run this code:
#
#      data = kite.request_access_token(
#          code="code_from_redirect",
#          secret="YOUR_APP_SECRET"
#      )
#      print(data['access_token'])
#
#    - Paste access token above as KITE_ACCESS_TOKEN value
#
# 3. APP SECRET:
#    - Go to your app settings at https://developers.kite.trade/
#    - Copy the App Secret
#    - Paste it above as KITE_APP_SECRET value
#
# ====================================================================
# SECURITY BEST PRACTICES:
# ====================================================================
#
# ✓ DO:
#   - Use environment variables in production
#   - Keep .env file in .gitignore
#   - Regenerate tokens monthly
#   - Use separate Zerodha account for bots
#   - Encrypt sensitive data if possible
#   - Monitor API usage regularly
#
# ✗ DON'T:
#   - Share .env file with anyone
#   - Commit .env to version control
#   - Hardcode credentials in code
#   - Use production API keys for testing
#   - Share access tokens in error reports
#   - Use weak passwords for Zerodha account
#
# ====================================================================
# OPTIONAL CONFIGURATIONS:
# ====================================================================
#
# For Telegram Alerts:
#   1. Create a Telegram bot: Message @BotFather on Telegram
#   2. Get your Chat ID: Message @userinfobot on Telegram
#   3. Add the token and chat ID below
#   4. Bot will send alerts when trades are executed
#
# For Email Alerts:
#   1. Create Gmail App Password (not regular password)
#   2. Set EMAIL_ENABLED=True
#   3. Add SMTP credentials
#   4. Bot will send email on trades
#
